parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress into Trunk and Rear Tire Well
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation in the trunk and rear tire well can cause rust, mold, and electrical issues, leading to safety hazards such as fogged-up tail lights, brake light failure, and respiratory problems.
symptoms: rusted spare tire and car jack

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Headlight Failure due to Poor Light Socket Design
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause hazardous night driving conditions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: vibration or arcing caused by light bulb locking mechanism assembly failure
and metal shavings present in the base of the reflector.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Manual Transmission Grinding and Popping Out of Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The grinding and popping out of gear can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded. This issue can also lead to premature wear of transmission components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: Grinding or klunking noise when shifting gears
transmission pops out of gear into neutral
gear grinds more frequently in cold temperatures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front strut assembly can cause a popping or knocking noise when turning, which can be a distraction to the driver and potentially lead to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Popping or knocking noise when turning
noise sounds like a bad axle
noise occurs when turning the wheels while the car is stationary.
